      • getRaw

        public String[] getRaw()
        Returns the underlying array of raw arguments that was given to this RawArguments upon instantiation.

        The array returned is the same array belonging to this object, meaning modifications to it will reflect in the methods of the object. Should usage of this be required, it is recommended to clone the array before usage or at least ensure that it is only being read from and not written to.

        Returns:
        the underlying array of raw arguments

      • drop

        public RawArguments drop(int n)
        Drops the earliest n raw arguments held by this RawArguments.

        Passing a number greater than the amount of raw arguments will throw an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException.

        Parameters:
        n - the amount of arguments to drop
        Returns:
        this RawArguments

      • getNextIndex

        public int getNextIndex()
        Returns:

      • peek

        public Optional<String> peek()
        Peeks at the next raw argument held by this RawArguments instance.

        This method does not advance the internal counter, meaning this will always return the same value until next() is called.

        If there are no more remaining arguments, this returns an empty optional. This method should be checked with in order to safely call next().

        Returns:
        the next parameter, without advancing?

      • peek

        public Optional<String> peek(int ahead)
        Peeks at the next raw argument held by this RawArguments instance.

        The ahead parameter specifies how far to look ahead. As an example, passing 1 will peek at the next argument that one would receive if they called next(). This also means passing 0 will retrieve the current argument, -1 will retrieve the previous, etc.

        This method does not advance the internal counter, meaning this will always return the same value until next() is called.

        If there are no more remaining arguments, this returns an empty optional. This method should be checked with in order to safely call next().

        Parameters:
        ahead - the offset index to peek at
        Returns:
        the next parameter, without advancing?

      • next

        public String next()
        Returns the next raw argument held by this RawArguments instance.

        This method will advance the internal counter. Consecutive calls on this method will eventually pass all arguments that were passed to this RawArguments instance upon instantiation..

        It is recommended to query peek() before calling this method, as an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException is thrown if the internal counter exceeds the maximum index.

        Returns:
        the next parameter
